Ask HN: The Simplest Graph Database?
text:
I'm looking for something with syntax like this:

  person was influenced by person

    weight 0.5

    url https://www.google.com

    source reporter

  person influenced person

  reference by person
How would you parse the above?

Simple:

1. Split by first and last space. First element is a variable/vertex, last element is a variable. Central "was influenced by" is an edge

2. Tabs = properties. In this case weight is a property of the connection as a whole. So you can think of it like: person_was_influenced_by_person.weight

So I want:

1. As close to English/Python as humanly possible.

2. No curly braces allowed!!11111!!

3. No "end" ... no need to "end" in python

4. No *

5. Maybe >, (, ), ... but dont overdo it.

6. So close to English a toddler could understand it

Ask HN: What’s the dark side of stoicism or its critique?
text:
I’m on my phone and am too slow in finding sources. With that said, I found quite some helpful thoughts over the years on HN about the dark side of meditation (people needing psychiatric help basically). Even with meditation it’s not talked about a lot. But so far, I have only read one good critique on stoicism (a few months ago to a year ago?). The main point there was that stoicism is individuallistically rooted. And it can impede collaboration or building a shared vision (potentially) because of it. I wish I had the source, because the author was more nuanced.

It just made me wonder: what are some critiques against stoicism? I’m a fan but given it’s all hype and no challenge, I’d like some challenge
